# ADR-005: Batman Understanding Engine

Status: Accepted

Date: 2026-06-27

---

# Context

Batman Student is not a chatbot.

Batman is an educational operating system that must understand students, validate requests, preserve learning context, and continuously improve while minimizing dependence on external AI providers.

Early implementations relied on rule-based parsing (regex, if/else) and direct LLM calls.

As the product grows across tutoring, quizzes, homework, planning and scheduling, this approach becomes difficult to maintain.

Batman requires a dedicated Understanding Layer.

---

# Decision

Batman adopts a Python-first Understanding Engine.

Python owns decision making.

LLMs assist only when Python cannot confidently interpret a request.

Every successful LLM interpretation becomes structured knowledge that Batman can reuse locally.

---

# Responsibilities

## Python Owns

• Workflow
• State Management
• Validation
• Governance
• Student Memory
• Knowledge Memory
• Routing
• Safety Rules
• Decision Making

Python is the final authority.

---

## LLM Owns

• Natural language understanding
• Semantic interpretation
• Ambiguity resolution
• Explanation generation
• Educational reasoning

LLM never owns workflow.

---

# Understanding Pipeline

Student

↓

Understanding

↓

Validation

↓

Memory

↓

