---

# Validation Principles

Batman never assumes.

Every interpreted request is validated.

Examples

Topic exists?

Difficulty supported?

Question count valid?

Chapter available?

If validation fails, Batman asks for clarification.

---

# Clarification

Batman asks only for missing information.

Example

Student

Quiz me on Light

↓

Batman

Which difficulty would you like?

Easy / Medium / Hard

Batman never asks questions whose answers are already known.

---

# Learning

Batman learns through structured memory.

Not through model retraining.

Examples

Optics → Light

Quick Test → Quiz

Challenge Me → Quiz

Practice → Quiz

Every confirmed mapping becomes reusable knowledge.

Future requests should avoid another LLM call whenever possible.

---

# Confidence

Every understanding result carries confidence.

High confidence

Proceed.

Medium confidence

Clarify.

Low confidence

Ask again.

Batman never guesses.

